The paper discusses time series classification using dictionary-based approaches, which involves techniques commonly used in machine learning and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves experimental analysis of algorithms, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) may also be relevant due to the use of time series data.
